1 0 0 1 54 668 Tm (oriented instead of generic.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 640 Tm (Problem Statement) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 626 Tm (The current PDP follow-up chips are too static. They often show the same FAQ and) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 612 Tm (browse actions regardless of the product, shopper intent, objections, or cart) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 598 Tm (state. This creates three issues:) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 570 Tm (1. The experience feels generic rather than tailored to the shopper.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 556 Tm (2. The chips do not consistently address the reason a shopper is hesitating.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 542 Tm (3. The chip set does not reliably move the shopper toward add-to-cart, a better) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 528 Tm (   fit alternative, or the next routine step.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 500 Tm (Product Goal) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 486 Tm (After a shopper lands on or interacts with a PDP, the NBA chips should help them) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 472 Tm (do one of the following:) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 444 Tm (1. Build confidence in the product they are viewing.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 430 Tm (2. Take the next step toward purchase.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 416 Tm (3. Discover the most relevant complementary product.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 402 Tm (4. Recover gracefully when the current product may not be the best fit.) Tj
1 0 0 1 54 374 Tm (Success Criteria) Tj
